<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1437,153,1368]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1197,1223]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2020" box="[563,691,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Apanteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longidiscus">
<emphasis box="[563,691,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">longidiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” derives from the Latin “longi-” and “discus”, referring to the disc of mesonotum rather long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1437,153,1368]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1269,1295]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityName="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2020" box="[670,966,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Apanteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prominens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[670,819,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">A. prominens</emphasis>
Liu &amp; Chen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[978,1069,1269,1295]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[978,1069,1269,1295]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differs in the following: T1 2.4× longer than hind width (hardly 2.0× in latter); ovipositor sheath 1.4× longer than length of hind tibia (nearly 1.2× in latter); and T2 over half length of T3 (not half in latter).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
